cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning (ML) technologies and their implementation in a mobile edge computing (MEC) framework. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of Federated Learning (FL) in a cellular network, which involves network infrastructure and communication protocols. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes a new FL protocol that manages clients based on their resource conditions, which involves system-level optimization and control. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
